# Build context excludes for the control-plane image (Dockerfile at repo root).
# The control-plane build needs go.mod/go.sum, the Go source under cmd/ and
# internal/, AND the skill package (skill/embed.go + the skill/ecu-computer-use
# tree are compiled into the binary via go:embed and served at /skill.zip).
# Everything below is irrelevant to it and only bloats the context (or leaks
# local state), so keep it out.

# VCS + editor/OS cruft.
.git/
.gitignore
.DS_Store

# Local control-plane state / secrets — never ship these into a layer.
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
*.env
.env
ecu.config
ecu.config.*
secrets/

# Go build output (the binary is produced inside the builder stage).
/ecu
dist/
*.test
*.out

# Spec / working drafts — reference material, not build inputs.
references/

# Packaging + deploy artifacts that are not Go build inputs.
install.sh
deploy/

# The instance (computer-use) image build context — a SEPARATE image
# (image/Dockerfile); not needed to build the control-plane binary.
image/

# The skill IS a control-plane build input now (go:embed — see the header):
# keep skill/embed.go and the skill/ecu-computer-use tree IN the context. Only
# the Python test file is never embedded; caches are skipped by go:embed anyway.
skill/ecu-computer-use/test_*.py

# Python caches (from the skill / tool server).
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
venv/

# Docs that are not build inputs.
*.md

# ...EXCEPT the skill docs that ARE embedded into the binary (go:embed bakes
# SKILL.md + references/api.md into /skill.zip). Re-include them, overriding the
# broad references/ and *.md excludes above — last match wins in .dockerignore.
!skill/ecu-computer-use/SKILL.md
!skill/ecu-computer-use/references/api.md
